a.title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.
a.xlink:title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.

a.title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.
a.xlink:title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept

a.title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.

a.title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.

a.title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].

a.title: ― ConceptRelationship: Relationship between a pair of concepts in a collection of concepts. Use controlled vocabulary provided in semantics to identify the type of relationship (relation, e.g. ParentChild, WholePart, etc.)

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.

a.title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.

a.title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.

a.title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.

a.title: ― PhysicalSegmentLayout: Used as an extension point in the description of the different layout styles of data structure descriptions.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalSegmentLayout: Used as an extension point in the description of the different layout styles of data structure descriptions.

a.title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.

a.title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.
a.xlink:title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.

a.title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).
a.xlink:title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).

a.title: ― LogicalRecord: Collection of instance variables.
a.xlink:title: ― LogicalRecord: Collection of instance variables.

a.title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.
a.xlink:title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.

a.title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).
a.xlink:title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).

a.title: ― ReferenceVariable: Variable that records values of multiple variables in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable value component.
a.xlink:title: ― ReferenceVariable: Variable that records values of multiple variables in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable value component.

a.title: ― RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.
a.xlink:title: ― RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.

a.title: ― DescriptorVariable: Variable that provides codes for variable identification in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable descriptor component.
a.xlink:title: ― DescriptorVariable: Variable that provides codes for variable identification in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable descriptor component.

a.title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.
a.xlink:title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.

a.title: ― UnitType: Unit type is a type or class of objects of interest (units).
a.xlink:title: ― UnitType: Unit type is a type or class of objects of interest (units).

a.title: ― Population: Universe with time and geography specified.
a.xlink:title: ― Population: Universe with time and geography specified.

a.title: ― KeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of the structure of a key definition.
a.xlink:title: ― KeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of the structure of a key definition.

a.title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of a dimensional key definition.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of a dimensional key definition.

a.title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.

a.title: ― ConceptualValue: Concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived which is associated to a single data instance.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualValue: Concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived which is associated to a single data instance.

a.title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.
a.xlink:title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.

a.title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.
